ude scale.<ref name=\"Kobe@en\">{{cite web|author=The City of Kobe|date=2008-01-01| url= http://www.city.kobe.jp/cityoffice/06/013/report/january.2008.pdf |title=STATISTICS|work=The Great Hanshin-Awaji Earthquake: Statistics and Restoration Progress|accessdate=2008-05-25}}</ref> The tremors lasted for approximately 20 seconds. The hypocenter of the earthquake was located {{convert|16|km|abbr=on}} beneath its [[epicenter]],<ref name=\"Kobe@en\"/> on the northern end of [[Awaji Island]], {{convert|20|km|abbr=on}} away from the city of [[Kobe]].\n|-\n| {{dts|1998|05|04}} || 7.5 ''M<sub>w</sub>'' || 0 ||1998 Ryukyu Islands earthquake || \u77f3\u57a3\u5cf6\u5357\u65b9\u6c96\u5730\u9707|| ''Ishigakijima nanp\u014d-oki jishin'' || {{coord|22.30|N|125.30|E|type:event}} || The epicentre was in the [[Philippine Sea]], far off the coast (260&nbsp;km from [[Ishigaki Island]], [[Japan]], 400&nbsp;km from [[Basco, Batanes|Basco]], [[Philippines]], and 425&nbsp;km from [[Hualian City|Hualian]], [[Taiwan]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://neic.usgs.gov/neis/eq_depot/1998/eq_980503/ |title=USGS Earthquake Hazards Program: Earthquake Report: Southeast of Taiwan |publisher=Neic.usgs.gov |accessdate=2010-07-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100202222802/http://neic.usgs.gov/neis/eq_depot/1998/eq_980503/ |archivedate=2010-02-02 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2001|03|24}} || 6.7 ''M<sub>w</sub>'' ||{{Hs|000002}}2 ||[[2001 Geiyo earthquake]] || 2001\u5e74\u82b8\u4e88\u5730\u9707 || ''Nisen-ichi-nen G\u0113yo Jishin'' || {{coord|34.083|N|128.020|E}} || \n|-\n| {{dts|2003|09|25}} || 8.3 ''M<sub>w</sub>'' ||{{Hs|000001}}1 ||[[2003 Hokkaid\u014d earthquake]] || 2003\u5e74\u5341\u52dd\u6c96\u5730\u9707 || ''Nisen-san-nen Tokachi-oki Jishin'' || {{coord|41.78|N|143.86|E}} || An earthquake occurring in [[Hokkaido]] on September 25, 2003. It measured 8.3 on the [[Moment magnitude scale]] and caused extensive damage to roads all around Hokkaido, several power outages, and landslides