seismic intensity]] of a strength 6 on Japan's [[Japan Meteorological Agency seismic intensity scale|''shindo'' scale]], but the quake was felt as far away as Tokyo.<ref name=\"jnr\"/> Eleven deaths and at least 1,000 injuries have been reported, and 342 buildings were completely destroyed, mostly older wooden structures.<ref name=\"jnr\"/><ref>[http://www.japannewsreview.com/society/chubu/20070723page_id=964 Niigata earthquake death toll rises to eleven] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103072457/http://www.japannewsreview.com/society/chubu/20070723page_id=964 |date=2013-11-03 }} [http://www.japannewsreview.com Japan News Review], July 23</ref><ref name=\"CNN Niigata\">{{cite news|title=Japanese nuke plant leaked after earthquake |url=http://www.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/asiapcf/07/16/japan.quake.ap/index.html |publisher=AP via CNN |date=2007-07-16 |accessdate=2007-07-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070810232526/http://www.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/asiapcf/07/16/japan.quake.ap/index.html#cnnSTCVideo |archivedate=August 10, 2007 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2008|06|14}} || 6.9 ''M<sub>w</sub>'' ||{{Hs|000012}}12 ||[[2008 Iwate\u2013Miyagi Nairiku earthquake]] || \u5ca9\u624b\u30fb\u5bae\u57ce\u5185\u9678\u5730\u9707 || ''Iwate Miyagi Nairiku Jishin'' || <span style=\"display:none\">Iwate Prefecture</span>about {{convert|1|km|mi|abbr=on}} east of Narusawa Onsen in northwest [[Iwate Prefecture]] || This earthquake struck the central [[T\u014dhoku region]], in northeastern [[Honsh\u016b]], Japan.<ref name=\"JMA-tremors\">{{cite web|url=http://www.seisvol.kishou.go.jp/cgi-bin/shindo_db.cgi?from_YYYY=2008&from_MM=06&from_DD=14&from_hh=08&from_mm=00&to_YYYY=2008&to_MM=06&to_DD=14&to_hh=12&to_mm=00&ORG_PID=14516&pref=0&minimum_shindo=1&max_count=50&PARAM_OK_DATE=%B8%A1%BA%F7%BC%C2%B9%D4|title=Result of searching the database of felt earthquakes|publisher=[[Japan Meteorological Agency]]|language=Japanese}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=Interne