kes/recenteqsww/Quakes/usc0001xgp.php |title=Magnitude 8.9 \u2013 Near the East coast of Honshu, Japan 2011 March 11 05:46:23 UTC |publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]] (USGS) |accessdate=11 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110312174548/http://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/recenteqsww/Quakes/usc0001xgp.php |archivedate=12 March 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.theworldreporter.com/2011/03/89-earthquake-in-japan-tsunami-warning.html|title = 8.9 Earthquake in Japan, Tsunami Warning to Russia, Taiwan and South East Asia|accessdate=11 March 2011|date=11 March 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"3news\">{{cite web|url=http://www.3news.co.nz/Japan-quake---7th-largest-in-recorded-history/tabid/417/articleID/201998/Default.aspx|title=Japan quake \u2013 7th largest in recorded history|accessdate=11 March 2011|date=11 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110316002513/http://www.3news.co.nz/Japan-quake---7th-largest-in-recorded-history/tabid/417/articleID/201998/Default.aspx|archive-date=2011-03-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was followed by a [[tsunami]] with waves of up to {{convert|10|m|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\"USGS1\" /> The disaster left thousands dead and inflicted extensive material damage to buildings and infrastructure that led to [[2011 Japanese nuclear accidents|significant accidents at four major nuclear power stations]].\n|-\n|  {{dts|2011|03|11}} <br/>06:25:50&nbsp;UTC || 7.1 ''M<sub>w</sub>'' ||0||[[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami|2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake]] aftershock || \u6771\u5317\u5730\u65b9\u592a\u5e73\u6d0b\u6c96\u5730\u9707([[Aftershock]])<br>(\u6771\u65e5\u672c\u5927\u9707\u707d) || ''T\u014dhokuchih\u014d Taiheiy\u014d Oki Jishin''<br>(''Higashi Nihon Dai-Shinsai'') || {{coord|38.106|N|144.553|E}}, depth 19.7&nbsp;km\n|{{cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/recenteqsww/Quakes/usc0001xig.php |title=Magnitude 7.1 - Off the East Coast of Honshu, JAPAN REGION |publisher=Ea